"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"388d372c","settings":{"editor":"<p data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\">Join Anthony Fasano, P.E., AEC PM and Peter Atherton, P.E. as they unveil the findings from <strong>The Present and Future of Work in Engineering and Architecture 2025<\/strong>. Learn what distinguishes the top employers in the industry and how their people-first strategies are shaping a more resilient, engaged, and high-performing workforce.<\/p><p>High-performing companies:<\/p><ol class=\"ProsemirrorEditor-list\"><li class=\"ProsemirrorEditor-listItem\" data-list-indent=\"1\" data-list-type=\"bulleted\"><p><strong>Invest in career growth<\/strong> \u2013 61% rate their training programs as excellent or above average (vs. just 3% at lower-performing companies).<\/p><\/li><li class=\"ProsemirrorEditor-listItem\" data-list-indent=\"1\" data-list-type=\"bulleted\"><p><strong>Boost engagement &amp; retention<\/strong> \u2013 Employees are <strong>5x more engaged<\/strong> and far less likely to leave.<\/p><\/li><li class=\"ProsemirrorEditor-listItem\" data-list-indent=\"1\" data-list-type=\"bulleted\"><p><strong>Align talent management with business goals<\/strong> \u2013 3.6x more effective at measuring performance, prioritizing output over hours worked.<\/p><\/li><\/ol><p>Top employers also recognize the critical role of employee well-being and technology adoption:<\/p><ol class=\"ProsemirrorEditor-list\"><li class=\"ProsemirrorEditor-listItem\" data-list-indent=\"1\" data-list-type=\"bulleted\"><p><strong>Lower burnout, higher satisfaction<\/strong> \u2013 Just 10% of employees report frequent burnout, compared to 39% at low-performing companies.<\/p><\/li><li class=\"ProsemirrorEditor-listItem\" data-list-indent=\"1\" data-list-type=\"bulleted\"><p><strong>Embrace AI &amp; emerging tech<\/strong> \u2013 A strategic advantage that drives both efficiency and talent attraction.<\/p><\/li><\/ol><p>Don't miss this opportunity to gain actionable insights that can transform your organization's approach to talent management and future-proof your workforce.<\/p><p>Register now to secure your spot!<\/p>","pa_condition_repeater":[],"premium_tooltip_text":"Hi, I'm a global tooltip.","premium_tooltip_position":"top,bottom"},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"6169b027","settings":{"editor":"<p data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\">Facilitator<\/p>","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":30,"sizes":[]},"typography_font_weight":"700","_margin":{"unit":"px","top":"0","right":"0","bottom":"0","left":"0","isLinked":false},"_padding":{"unit":"px","top":"30","right":"0","bottom":"0","left":"0","isLinked":false},"pa_condition_repeater":[],"premium_tooltip_text":"Hi, I'm a global tooltip.","premium_tooltip_position":"top,bottom","__globals__":{"text_color":"globals\/colors?id=primary"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"8097002","settings":{"editor":"<h2 class=\"fl-heading\">Bob Kelleher | Employee Engagement Group<\/h2>","_margin":{"unit":"px","top":"0","right":"0","bottom":"0","left":"0","isLinked":false},"_padding":{"unit":"px","top":"0","right":"0","bottom":"0","left":"0","isLinked":false},"pa_condition_repeater":[],"premium_tooltip_text":"Hi, I'm a global tooltip.","premium_tooltip_position":"top,bottom"},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"17aa2f09","settings":{"editor":"<p><a href=\"https:\/\/engineeringmanagementinstitute.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/03\/Bob-Kelleher.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-74096 size-medium\" src=\"https:\/\/engineeringmanagementinstitute.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/03\/Bob-Kelleher-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" \/><\/a>Bob Kelleher is the President and Founder of The Employee Engagement Group and is an award-winning speaker and thought leader on employee engagement, workforce trends, and leadership. Regularly featured on national media, including appearances on CNBC, CBS Radio, and Fox Radio, Bob is also a frequent writer in many national publications, including Business Week, Fortune, HR Executive, NBC News, Incentive Magazine, CNET, The Boston Globe, and Training Magazine.<\/p><p>Bob is the author of the best seller Louder Than Words, 10 Practical Employee Engagement Steps... that Drive Results!, the critically acclaimed, Creativeship, An Employee Engagement and Leadership Fable, Employee Engagement for Dummies, and the recently released I-Engage, Your Personal Engagement Roadmap, quickly climbing the charts on both Amazon and Barnes and Noble.<\/p><p>Before becoming an author\/speaker\/consultant, Bob spent 25 years building award-winning engagement cultures, as the Chief Human Capital Officer for AECOM, nowa 95,000-employee Fortune200 professional services firm with hundreds of global officers, and as EVP and COO of ENSR, an international environmental consulting firm.<\/p>","_padding":{"unit":"px","top":"0","right":"0","bottom":"0","left":"0","isLinked":false},"pa_condition_repeater":[],"premium_tooltip_text":"Hi, I'm a global tooltip.","premium_tooltip_position":"top,bottom"},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"44903146","settings":{"editor":"<p data-pm-slice=\"1 1 []\">Presenters<\/p>","typography_typography":"custom","typography_font_size":{"unit":"px","size":30,"sizes":[]},"typography_font_weight":"700","_margin":{"unit":"px","top":"0","right":"0","bottom":"0","left":"0","isLinked":false},"_padding":{"unit":"px","top":"30","right":"0","bottom":"0","left":"0","isLinked":false},"pa_condition_repeater":[],"premium_tooltip_text":"Hi, I'm a global tooltip.","premium_tooltip_position":"top,bottom","__globals__":{"text_color":"globals\/colors?id=primary"}},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"418275b9","settings":{"editor":"<h2 class=\"fl-heading\">Peter Atherton, P.E.<\/h2>","_margin":{"unit":"px","top":"0","right":"0","bottom":"0","left":"0","isLinked":false},"_padding":{"unit":"px","top":"0","right":"0","bottom":"0","left":"0","isLinked":false},"pa_condition_repeater":[],"premium_tooltip_text":"Hi, I'm a global tooltip.","premium_tooltip_position":"top,bottom"},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"30ec8f3","settings":{"editor":"<p><a href=\"https:\/\/engineeringmanagementinstitute.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/Peter-C-Atherton.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-73321 size-medium\" src=\"https:\/\/engineeringmanagementinstitute.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/02\/Peter-C-Atherton-300x300.jpg\" alt=\"ActionsProve, LLC\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" \/><\/a>Pete is the President and Founder of ActionsProve, LLC, author of Reversing Burnout. How to Immediately Engage Top Talent and Grow! A Blueprint for Professionals and Business Owners, and creator of the I.M.P.A.C.T. process. Pete is also the host of the AEC Leadership Today Podcast.<\/p><p>ActionsProve helps AEC leaders and firms grow and advance their success through modern and new era focused strategic planning and advisory, executive coaching, leadership and management team development, performance-based employee engagement, and differentiated impact design.<\/p><p>Prior to founding ActionsProve, and for more than 20 years, Pete was a very successful and accomplished professional civil engineer. Pete sold his engineering firm ownership to focus on designing systems for you and your organization to grow and prosper in more relevant and effective ways. For over a dozen years, Pete has also been serving in multiple capacities in the non-profit sector to achieve both local and global impact.<\/p>","_padding":{"unit":"px","top":"0","right":"0","bottom":"50","left":"0","isLinked":false},"pa_condition_repeater":[],"premium_tooltip_text":"Hi, I'm a global tooltip.","premium_tooltip_position":"top,bottom"},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"69b65a06","settings":{"editor":"<h2 class=\"fl-heading\">Anthony Fasano, P.E., AEC PM | Engineering Management Institute<\/h2>","_margin":{"unit":"px","top":"0","right":"0","bottom":"0","left":"0","isLinked":false},"_padding":{"unit":"px","top":"0","right":"0","bottom":"0","left":"0","isLinked":false},"pa_condition_repeater":[],"premium_tooltip_text":"Hi, I'm a global tooltip.","premium_tooltip_position":"top,bottom"},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"},{"id":"79628188","settings":{"editor":"<p><a href=\"https:\/\/engineeringmanagementinstitute.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/Anthony-Fasano.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright wp-image-55130\" src=\"https:\/\/engineeringmanagementinstitute.org\/wp-content\/uploads\/2023\/01\/Anthony-Fasano.jpg\" alt=\"EMI- Your Engineering Career\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" \/><\/a><\/p><p>Most AEC organizations are too busy to focus on attracting, developing, and retaining talented professionals, making it hard to grow. Through his work at EMI, Fasano utilizes a proven framework to help organizations, both public and private, build professional development plans, programs, and tools that help them attract, build, AND maintain strong teams and grow sustainably.<\/p><p>Fasano has written a bestselling book entitled\u00a0<b><i>Engineer Your Own Success\u00a0<\/i><\/b><i>(by IEEE-Wiley Press)<\/i>, and under his stewardship, EMI has built a massive content platform including 10 active podcasts, 3 YouTube channels, and a popular blog dedicated to helping AEC professionals become better managers and leaders.<\/p>","_padding":{"unit":"px","top":"0","right":"0","bottom":"0","left":"0","isLinked":false},"pa_condition_repeater":[],"premium_tooltip_text":"Hi, I'm a global tooltip.","premium_tooltip_position":"top,bottom"},"elements":[],"isInner":false,"widgetType":"text-editor","elType":"widget"}],"isInner":true,"elType":"column"}],"isInner":true,"elType":"section"}],"isInner":false,"elType":"column"}],"isInner":false,"elType":"section"}],"settings":{"template":"elementor_canvas"},"metadata":{"_yoast_wpseo_estimated-reading-time-minutes":"4","_yoast_wpseo_content_score":"90","be_title_toggle_hide":"1","disable_sitewide_popup":"a:1:{i:0;s:4:\"true\";}","_yoast_wpseo_wordproof_timestamp":"","_yoast_wpseo_meta-robots-noindex":"1","_yoast_wpseo_meta-robots-nofollow":"1"}}